apca (pakistan railway's wing) ky zaer-e-ehtemaam bamaqam pakistan railways divisional superintendent office, rawalpindi opposite rawalpindi railway station, ho ga. tamam dosto (especially islamabad TRANSLATED IN ENGLISH: Assalam-o-Alaikum, friends. Yesterday, we asked for your opinion on starting a protest for the upgradation of ministerial posts in federal and provincial areas where upgradation hasn't happened yet. From last evening until now, according to the response we've received, 99.7% of people have advised us to start the protest, and they have also expressed confidence in participating in this protest. As you all know, there is a long history of struggle behind the provinces where upgradation has happened. They say that until the child cries, the mother doesn't give milk, so no one will give you your rights just by placing a plate. Courage and passion are needed to claim your rights, which your friends from KP and Punjab have shown and achieved success. For us, your opinion is very important, so today we announce the start of our protest. In this regard, the first protest will be held on 14th January 2016 at 11:00 am, under the auspices of APCA (Pakistan Railway's Wing), at the Divisional Superintendent Office of Pakistan Railways, Rawalpindi, opposite Rawalpindi Railway Station. We request all friends (especially Islamabad Secretariat Employees Association, APCA Bait-ul-Mal, and IESCO Employees Association) to come out for their rights and make sure to participate in this protest. Because if we don't come out now, then this issue will remain unresolved. Insha'Allah, for more details, please contact the protest coordinator at 0300-2341366.
